title: Polar Visible Imaging System (VIS) Earth Camera Images at ~4 minute cadence - Louis A. Frank (The University of Iowa)

info.x_cadence_note: Counts based on variable 'Epoch' in https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/sp_phys/data/polar/vis/vis_earth-camera-calibrated/1996/po_vis_earth-camera-calibrated_1996043000_v01.cdf. The most common cadence occurred for 35.0000% of the 21 timesteps. Cadence = 53500 [ms] = PT53.5S.
info.contact: Louis A. Frank @ The University of Iowa

parameters.name: Image_Counts_Raw
parameters.description: Uncleaned 256 x 256 Ultra-Violet Image (quasi-logarithmically compressed counts)

parameters.name: Image_Counts_Clean
parameters.description: Cleaned and Filtered 256 x 256 Ultra-Violet Image (quasi-logarithmically compressed counts)
parameters.units: Cleaned UV Intensity in QLC Counts

parameters.name: Mapped_ImageO
parameters.description: --> (USE SHORT TIME SPANS) With geographic map overlay. This variable is a 'virtual' variable that is computed using the function alternate_view (see https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/pub/software/cdawlib/source/virtual_funcs.pro) on the with inputs of the variables ['Image_Counts_Clean', 'Geo_Lat', 'Geo_Lon']. Note that some COMPONENTS may not be available from the HAPI interface. They are accessible from the raw CDF files, however.
